Contact Us Why Choose Us? Wide Variety We pride ourselves on the ability to make any print item needed for your business - from name badges and signs to mugs and t-shirts. Best in the Nation Founded in 2008 and based out of Downtown Fargo, ND. With a second facility for production in the industrial park of North Fargo. Highest Quality We create affordable, professional office signs and conference room signs with a clean and contemporary look that will easily elevate your business's professionalism, efficiency, and communications. Two-Day Turnaround We offer a quick two-day turnaround on all standard products. Some exceptions will apply and it does not include art approval time. Our Process Custom Order Start creating your custom design. Not sure where to start? Contact us and we can walk you through it. Proofing We’ll get to work designing your custom signs, badges, vinyl or whatever you may need. Review We send you a digital proof to make sure it’s up to your exact expectations. Production Once approved, we will begin production in our Fargo, ND based facility. These wayfinding signs are effective at marking the way to key locations to help guests and personel avoid confusion in your business or office, especially in larger and complex floors where guests are likely to be unfamiliar with where they need to go. We provide free logos, arrows and custom text on all our office & directory signs. Send logos to artwork@officesigncompany.com or request a digital sign proof. Types of Hallway Signs -- Our 2-sided corridor flags, door flags and business directory signs install easily and are fully customizable with text, logos and more at no extra charge. Show the way to any restroom, suite room or offices with our custom directional signs and projecting wall signs. Fully Customizable Hallway Signs Can't find the right hallway, wall projecting, or directional signs that you need on our web site? We design custom wayfinding solutions every day, simply e-mail us at service@officesigncompany.com or call us with sign questions, sign quotes or to request a digital proof of your vision. Office Sign Mounting Options Looking to mount your custom sign to a wall or door in your office? Our 15+ years of signmaking have taught us a thing or two about how to install an office sign. Under each product option on our website, you’ll be able to choose the mounting option that works best for your needs - and most are available at no added cost! Review the video on mounting options, contact our team to inquire more, or learn about each mounting option in the section below. Contact Us Double-Sided Foam Tape Our industrial-strength, double-sided foam tape creates a secure bond between your sign and mounting surface, and is available in multiple thicknesses (which our quality control department will automatically affix based on your sign’s size). Usage Information: best to use on flat, non-porous walls or doors. Purchase 3M Clear Tape (Glass Tape) This mounting option is easy-to-use, provides high strength and long-term durability, and (best of all) will go undetected on the backside of your sign when installed on glass. Our 3M Clear Tape is the perfect sign mounting option for any window or glass installs. Usage Information: best used on internal windows or glass surfaces. Purchase Velcro This hook & loop velcro mounting tape is a good option to consider if you plan to routinely change out your signage. For example, if you have a sign on your wall that you routinely swap out for another sign, velcro is a great solution for you. Usage Information: best to use for low-bond, easy-to-replace sign installs. Purchase 3M Command Strips This mounting option is arguably the easiest to install and the easiest to remove without tearing paint or damaging a wall or door. Similar to our velcro solution, this mounting option also is a good one to consider for temporary (or replaceable) signage installs. Usage Information: best used on painted, stained or varnished wood or walls. Purchase Magnetic Mounting Affixing your sign to a metal substrate, wall, or door? Magnetic tape is a great option for you! This mounting option is available for several standard products or can be requested custom for any sign that you’d like to readily remove and reapply to walls and doors. Usage Information: ensure that you will be mounting the sign to a door or wall with magnetic properties. Purchase Cubicle Fangs These metal sign fasteners are an ideal hanging and fastening device if your sign will be installed to a fabric substrate or cubicle cloth. If you are looking to put employee nameplates on cubicles - you’ve found your ideal, low-cost mounting option. Usage Information: ensure that you will be using this on a fabric or cloth wall or partition. Purchase Stand-Offs Stand-offs are a great mounting option for both interior and exterior signage. They cover up screws used to affix a sign to a wall, and provide a gap between the sign and the wall for a polished, professional look. Easy to install & great for replacing signs (and utilizing the same stand-offs for the new sign). Usage Information: will require you to drill holes in your wall in order to mount. Purchase Hanging Cables Looking to hang your signs from the ceiling? We’ve got the cables and hooks required for the job! This mounting option works perfectly for directional, wayfinding signage. Usage Information: hardware for attaching cables to the ceiling must be purchased separately. Purchase Hanging Cables Looking to hang your signs from the ceiling? Restroom Sign Options - Our Restroom signs are available in a variety of materials and styles, include brushed metal, wood or frosted acrylic, and can be customized in a number of ways including custom text and adding bathroom directional arrows, branding or custom graphics. Frosted Acrylic signs have been a popular choice recently for adding a contemporary look to offices, spas and restaurants. ADA Bathroom Signs - We offer many options for ADA braille bathroom signs, including most of our popular standard restroom signs below. We have over 25 years experience in creating quality, name plates, fully-customizable conference room signs and sliding in/out meeting signs, executive office signs, restroom signage, ADA signage, receptionist desk bars, full color logo nameplates and employee office door signs and cubicle signs. Our brushed metal series of office signs, name plates and door signs are available in silver, gold, copper or white metal nameplates. We also stock wood tone office signs and sign name plates in virtually ANY color to match your existing office signs or to enhance your interior design - we can print and match any color on our white plates to match any office decor. Our white office sign plates are coated for dry erase use. Most of our products have frame color options to accurately match the colors in your business environment. Every architectural sign and name plate can be personalized with board room names, doctors room names, titles, employee names, personnel, no smoking, copay info, conference room numbers and so on. The text, corporate logos and graphics on our signs is permanent and the signs wipe clean easily. Thank you for visiting www.officesigncompany.com, a company dedicated to professionals seeking quality interior office signage and medical name plate signs. Cool office signs fabricated right in the heart of beautiful downtown Fargo, North Dakota. At Office Sign Company of Fargo, every one of our signs, name plates, and badges can be personalized with any text, full color logo or graphic at no additional charge - we don't store huge quantities of preprinted, generic signs. Using your custom text we create your own custom waiting room signs, exam room signs, corporate badges, elevator signs, dental office signs and conference room signage - or simply show off your corporate colors with full color corporate logos on metal plates. All signage comes with free mounting hardware of your choice. We offer office signs in brushed metal as well as engraved office signs in virtually any color. We stand behind our sign products with pride and service. We serve businesses and corporations of any size with the highest quality office signs. We also manufacture signs for the US government under our GSA Contract GS-03F-0070X. GSA Buyers and military purchasing agents are welcome here. We take pride in producing signs that exhibit an unmatched blend of aesthetics, functionality and fine craftsmanship. We provide all customers with unparalleled quality and value, achieved through our personalized service, innovative product solutions, and continuous development and empowerment of our employees. Additionally, we strive to keep American manufacturing alive by creating jobs, driving creativity and collaboration, and building strong and trusted relationships with our customers, vendors, and local community. We pride in being one of the best places to work in the Fargo-Moorhead area because of our fun and upbeat work culture, and growing number of employee incentives and perks. In 2015, The FM Chamber recognized Office Sign Company as Small Business of the Year. POSITION OVERVIEWWe seek to hire a positive, energetic, and self-motivated Layout Artist to design customer sign orders. A top priority will be the creation of digital proofs to support a fast turnaround time for our customer’s requests. This position will support customer inquiries and order/proof layout updates via phone and email. This individual must be comfortable and experienced with Adobe Illustrator and Photoshop. TYPE Full-time SALARY/WAGES Dependent on experience. Responsibilities:● Create and submit customer-driven digital sign proofs that communicate messages clearly with an emphasis on strong design while providing the best solutions for our customers in a fast-paced environment. ● Follow up on customer feedback and proof revisions with timely, professional, and courteous correspondence and updates. ● Shift focus as needed to maintain desirable turnaround times in all order queues. ● Initiative to quickly gain intimate knowledge of our products, materials, and services. Secondary Responsibilites:● Take the initiative to train in production departments so you can be of assistance to Vinyl, Quality Control, Engraving, or Sublimation if they are under-staffed and requesting help. ● Answer customer phone calls with questions pertaining to design. ● Contribute to departmental discussions about operations and growth. ● Assist with excellent design to support our marketing efforts and product prototypes. ● Be an active part of community outreach (including being involved in our volunteering efforts and Culture committee.) ● Attend trade shows, local events, networking groups, and other community functions. ● Research industry trends and educate co-workers on the research you’ve found. ● Additional duties assigned by management. ● HAVE A DAMN GOOD TIME!! Make our company better because of your employment here. Qualifications ● Proficiency in Adobe Illustrator and Adobe Photoshop are basic requirements of this job position. ● Mastery of design principles, especially as applied to text/print layout and font treatments. ● Understanding of layout principles. POSITION OVERVIEWAs a Customer Account Manager at Office Sign Company, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring that all customer experiences are exceptional. You will be responsible for building and maintaining strong relationships with our clients, anticipating their needs, and providing solutions that exceed their expectations. This role requires a highly motivated and results-oriented individual with a deep commitment to quality and customer satisfaction. TYPE Full-time: Monday to Friday SALARY/WAGES D.O.E. Shipping Policy Return Policy FAQs About Us Frame Colors Mounting Options FAQs I don't see what I'm looking For. Can you make my custom sign? At Office Sign Company, we make custom signs each and every day. We try to showcase many of our best-selling signs on our website, but we simply have so much more to offer. Do not hesitate to contact us for variations of what we currently offer online, but also to challenge a very creative sign production team on your next custom sign. What is your production time on orders? Our standard production time is 2 - 4 business days on all orders, but many orders are fabricated within 24 hours (not including shipping time - please review our FedEx ship times to your area here ). We also offer expedited shipping options and Rush Options for those needing a name badge, or any sign we make in a hurry. Office Sign Company is not open on weekends and we do not account for weekends and holidays in our production times. For custom products that are not seen on our website and other extenuating circumstances, the production times will be longer. Still, we try our best to have all orders produced within two business days of an order being placed. We also work exceptionally well at expediting orders if a customer has a day set in mind that they need their product in hand. Keep in mind, it is the customer's responsibility to communicate need by dates for any order. Please communicate order needs by dates, all while considering shipping times and weekends in your sign needs. Do you provide digital proofs for signs? Yes, we do - and it is entirely free of charge. We understand our customers' need for a digital representation of their sign either before an order is placed, or before it is moved into production. If you are interested in having our team create a digital proof, please send your request to artwork@officesigncompany.com and include the following information: Sign or product you would like to have proofed Vector art file (will explain a few questions down) of your logo Text, font, and other pertinent details for the product Our talented team of graphic designers is happy to work with customers until they are satisfied with how their designs look. If you put in a request for a digital proof, it is our goal to have that digital proof (in the form of a .pdf) sent your way within 24 hours. Once the proof is approved, orders will move forward. Is there an extra charge for customization? No. There are no additional charges for custom text, logos, colors and fonts that are used for products you order from Office Sign Company. Personalization is built into our costs on our website, so you will never be surprised with any hidden fees related to customizing your products. We understand that every individual and business has different needs. Customizing your sign to align with your workplace aesthetics or your company's brand is a crucial element in the implementation of new signage solutions. If you have any questions regarding customization, please feel free to contact our service team to find out more! How can I receive a quote? Although many customers call in to receive pricing on custom signs and bulk quantities, we can only send quotes through email. This makes sure that both the customer and our internal team have everything in writing as it relates to pricing of signage products. If you are looking to have a quote on a custom sign or a wholesale / bulk quantity, please reach out to our service team with your request and they will promptly provide you with a quote. We are committed to protecting the personal information you share with us. This privacy policy outlines the types of personal information we collect, how we use that information, and how we protect your privacy. Information we collectWhen you visit our website, we may collect certain personal information from you, such as your name, email address, mailing address, and phone number. We may also collect information about the products you purchase from us, your billing and shipping addresses, and your payment information. In addition, we may collect information about your use of our website, such as your IP address and browser type. How we use your informationWe use the information we collect to fulfill your orders and to improve our products and services. We may also use your information to send you promotional emails or newsletters, if you have opted-in to receive them. If you no longer wish to receive promotional emails from us, you can unsubscribe at any time. We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us with processing orders, shipping products, and providing customer service. These service providers are contractually obligated to keep your information confidential and to only use your information for the purposes of providing services to Office Sign Company. In addition, we may disclose your information if required by law, or if we believe that such disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process. How we protect your informationWe take the security of your personal information seriously. We use industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information, including SSL encryption for all data transmissions. We also limit access to your personal information to only those employees who need it to perform their jobs. While we take reasonable precautions to safeguard your personal information, no transmission of data over the internet is guaranteed to be completely secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the security of your information transmitted to our website and you do so at your own risk. Changes to our privacy policyWe may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices. If we make any material changes, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice on our website prior to the change becoming effective. We encourage you to periodically review this page for the latest information on our privacy practices. Contact usIf you have any questions about our privacy policy or the practices of our website, please contact us at Service@OfficeSignCompany.com. Close × ! Shipped Fast. We pride ourselves on shipping your office signs, interior signage and desk name plates as fast as possible. Including shipments to Canada and International Sign Shipments. We are proud to announce that we are a Non-Resident Importer to our Canadian customers. Our strict quality control production procedures do take precedence over quicker shipping. We work hard to ship accurate, precisely fabricated sign solutions with a goal of shipping within 2 - 4 business days from the time your order is placed. We will continue to strive to provide your signage solutions as quickly as possible, as we continue to navigate the global pandemic. Please note custom signage and requests may slow order fabrication. We are pleased to announce that as of January 2019, we are now offering FREE GROUND SHIPPING as an option on all online orders that are $199.00 or more within the contiguous United States! Our Free Ground Shipping option, which can be selected at checkout, is delivered via FedEx and will be processed via standard FedEx ground times. Please review the map below to learn more about the length of shipping time! The Service Maps and charts are a general representations of transit. For more accurate transit quotes contact service. Note: if you are a local customer, purchasing custom sign products, or live outside of the contiguous United States, you may not be eligible for free ground shipping. Please take into consideration our office sign products are custom made to each order. Nearly every office sign order is shipped within 2 - 4 business days if not sooner, but many of our larger sign orders may take additional time to complete - due to the custom nature of each of our sign solutions. We use standard ground (FedEx) shipping methods and expedited shipping options and have a very low flat shipping rate. We offer RUSH shipping options at the customers expense. Please call us at (701) 526-3835 or email us at service@officesigncompany.com for expedited shipping options and rates. If you live in Fargo, North Dakota, you can pick up your order locally at the best sign shop in town. Each of our office name plates and building way-finding signs are custom crafted to your personalization - please bear in mind the size of your sign order may add additional production time and we appreciate your patience. We offer basic shipping and expedited options for International as well as Canadian sign orders - we have upgraded our Canadian shipments and are a Non-Resident Importer (NRI) to our Canadian customers: Canada Shipping. Non Resident Importer. Landed cost rate displayed (Includes Freight, Brokerage, Duty and Tax). No additional fees upon delivery. Rate shown covers 2-day shipping International orders will be reviewed and shipped at the discretion of Office Sign Company. Customers are responsible for imports VAT, clearance fees, or any other charges incurred during international transit. Order with confidence from our secure web site - offering the finest in conference room signs, office door nameplates, restroom signs, meeting and board room signs, and any custom office sign, waiting room or wall sign that you can imagine - even full color nameplates or colors that will match your office decor. PLEASE NOTE: Incomplete shipping addresses and addresses that change during shipping WILL incur additional shipping charges without warning. UPS and FedEx charge us when shipping addresses contain missing suite numbers, etc. and we must pass these charges along to customers that do not supply us with a complete ship to address. We do our best to manufacture all Rush and Expedited orders as quickly as possible. If you are looking to expedite your sign order, please call our Customer Success team at 701-526-3835 to submit this request. We are able to accommodate nearly all deadlines, and take a great deal of pride in our ability to turn your product around quickly. If you have any concerns about receiving your item(s) on time, please contact our Customer Success staff directly, and we’ll be happy to walk you through our Rush/Expedited Shipping options. For that reason alone, every sign product we offer is manufactured with your satisfaction in mind. Prior to a sign leaving our facility, it is carefully checked by our quality control staff to ensure that the product is free of any defect in material or workmanship. In the rare event that an office sign does show up with defect or damage, please notify our customer service team by emailing service@officesigncompany.com or call us at 701-526-3835 within 30 days of order receipt if you wish to replace or be refunded for a damaged sign.
